summary: Alexander Zverev has reached the French Open final after settling a domestic abuse case brought by his ex-girlfriend. This is Zverev's fourth consecutive French Open semifinal appearance and he will face Rafael Nadal in the final.

name: Brumbies
summary: The ACT Brumbies defeated the Highlanders in the Super Rugby Pacific semifinals, earning a place in the tournament's final four. The match was a thrilling encounter, with the Brumbies overcoming a determined Highlanders team to secure a 35-25 victory. The Brumbies' triumph marks the first time an Australian team has reached the Super Rugby semifinals since 2020. Key moments in the match included a superb skill display from the Brumbies' flyer, which helped secure their victory. The result sets up a highly anticipated semifinal clash between the Brumbies and the Blues, while the Hurricanes will face the Chiefs in the other semifinal. The Highlanders, despite their loss, played with great determination and showcased their potential for future success.

name: Shannon Cox
summary: Former Collingwood player Shannon Cox has been charged in connection with a fatal crash in Western Australia that left two elderly women dead and a 12-year-old girl injured. Cox was allegedly driving the vehicle that collided with the women's car in the Wheatbelt region on Saturday. The victims, aged 78 and 85, were pronounced dead at the scene. The young girl was airlifted to Perth Children's Hospital with serious injuries. Cox, 47, has been charged with two counts of dangerous driving occasioning death and one count of dangerous driving occasioning grievous bodily harm. He appeared in Perth Magistrates Court on Monday and was granted bail. The investigation is ongoing.

name: William Anders
summary: William Anders, the celebrated astronaut who captured the iconic "Earthrise" image during the Apollo 8 mission, has tragically passed away in a plane crash off Vancouver Island. The news has been confirmed by multiple sources, including CTV News, NASA, ABC News, USA TODAY, NBC News, Yahoo News Canada, The Guardian, PBS NewsHour, The Washington Post, and CBS News. The 90-year-old was identified as the pilot of the aircraft that crashed into a lake, triggering search and rescue efforts. Anders's passing marks a significant loss for the space community and the world at large.
